I"f<h2 id="find-texture-locations-im-materialx-image-vops">Find Texture Locations im materialX Image VOPs</h2>
<p>Useful for when you have a large scene that is returning missing texture references but you donâ€™t know where.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>import hou
import os

texture = hou.ui.readInput(message="Texture Name.ext")

nodes = hou.vopNodeTypeCategory().nodeType("mtlximage").instances()

for node in nodes:
    if os.path.basename(node.parm("file").eval()) == texture[1]:
        print(node.path())
</code></pre></div></div>
